Definition.WordDefinition: Genitals \Gen"i*tals\, n. pl. [From {Genital}, a.: cf. L. genitalia.] The organs of generation; the sexual organs; the private parts. [1913 Webster]
genitals n : external sex organ [syn: {genitalia}, {genital organ}, {private parts}, {privates}, {crotch}]
